<!DOCTYPE issue SYSTEM "lwg-issue.dtd">

<issue num="3751" status="WP">
<title>Missing feature macro for <tt>flat_set</tt></title>
<section><sref ref="[version.syn]"/></section>
<submitter>Barry Revzin</submitter>
<date>04 Aug 2022</date>
<priority>99</priority>

<discussion>
<p>
As pointed out by <a href="https://lists.isocpp.org/sg10/2022/07/0834.php">Casey Carter</a>, 
while there is a feature macro for <tt>flat_map</tt> in <paper num="P0429"/>, there is 
no corresponding macro for flat_set in <paper num="P1222"/>. We should add one.
</p>

<note>2022-08-23; Reflector poll</note>
<p>
Set status to Tentatively Ready after 10 votes in favour during reflector poll.
</p>

<note>2022-11-12 Approved at November 2022 meeting in Kona. Status changed: Voting &rarr; WP.</note>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<ol>

<li><p>Modify <sref ref="[version.syn]"/> as indicated:</p>

<blockquote>
<pre>
#define __cpp_lib_flat_map  202207L <i>// also in &lt;flat_map&gt;</i>
<ins>#define __cpp_lib_flat_set  202207L <i>// also in &lt;flat_set&gt;</i></ins>
</pre>
</blockquote>
</li>

</ol>
</resolution>

</issue>
